Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.70,0:06:35.29,Baribari,,0,0,0,,{\fade(1500,1500)\blur0.7\fs48\c&H000000&\fscx117.955\fscy120\fax-0.3\pos(341,410)}The Legend of Revving Engines
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.70,0:06:35.29,Baribari,,0,0,0,,{\fade(1500,1500)\blur0.7\fs48\c&HFFFFFF&\fscx117.955\fscy120\fax-0.3\pos(342,411)}The Legend of Revving Engines
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.27,0:06:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is snowing hard, huh? \NGuess I won't be riding any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.05,0:06:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That bike's the only thing on\N your mind, isn't it, Hideyoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.99,0:07:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Y'know, I heard there was a really \Nbad crash on that pass you drive on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.84,0:07:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Some things never change.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.55,0:07:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of idiots\N on the road, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.85,0:07:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's that dangerous there, \Nthen maybe you should stop going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.91,0:07:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.06,0:07:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hideyoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.03,0:07:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I... get kinda scared sometimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.74,0:07:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially when I'm waiting for you to come back from your morning ride... I just think...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.27,0:07:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I just think,\N if something ever hap—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.89,0:07:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.06,0:07:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go already.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.41,0:07:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get so worked \Nup over nothin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.43,0:07:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoyo, please understand, \NI'm doing this for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.41,0:08:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What do {\i1}you{\i0} want?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.65,0:08:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with {\i1}you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.36,0:08:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatcha starin' for?! {顔つけた - is likt to glare at someone / to give them a dirty look}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.78,0:08:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Lookin' at you makes \Nme wanna hurl!{目がくさりよる - more osaka-ben by look of it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.84,0:08:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Who lit your fuse today?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.80,0:08:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,C'mon, you wanna piece of me?! {I'm not sure the ippen but is right, I'd just assume it's 一遍ぶっち殺してのか}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.20,0:08:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What? So that's \Nwhy you're all sulky?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.42,0:08:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You two belong in \Nkindergarten, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.78,0:08:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun! Hiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.15,0:08:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here, there's \Nsomething I wanna talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.15,0:09:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You know about the 4-hour endurance race\N held at Suzuka over the summer, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.66,0:09:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and I know about the\N 8-hour race the day after.{ye, the four hour one was for the 'amateurs' the day before the Suz 8 hour for the pros}{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suzuka_8_Hours}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.31,0:09:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.22,0:09:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking of entering it under the Ichinose Racing Team.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.56,0:09:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.71,0:09:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.52,0:09:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Do you really mean that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.33,0:09:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and I need \Nthree more riders.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.70,0:09:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You serious about this? {changed as he's using the potential form as he doesn't believe it yet. Just roll w/ it for now}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.98,0:09:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll race as two pairs, \Nand I'll be driver number four.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.55,0:09:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Count me in! Even if I've gotta\Nwork with that stupid beanpole!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.41,0:09:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.37,0:09:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya heard me! I don't jus' race \Nfor fun like you rich kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.97,0:09:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Like hell I'm working with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.03,0:09:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.30,0:09:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Please enter the \Nrace, just this once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.10,0:09:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.89,0:09:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.21,0:10:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When did I say I wouldn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.36,0:10:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.82,0:10:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with him?! I thought he'd rather die than do something like that! {Gun's confused he is since Hideyoshi's typically too proud to do something like that}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.83,0:10:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I could never do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.26,0:10:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But he can do what I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.89,0:10:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He was way more \Ninto that than I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.40,0:10:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When I see how much\N he really wants it, {貪欲}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.73,0:10:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I really do look like some\N amateur doing this for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.65,0:10:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.75,0:10:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The cold winter had passed,\N and with that, a warm spring had arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.86,0:10:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I really wish I had a bike license...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.37,0:10:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But my mom said...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.23,0:10:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Not on your life! \NOnly hooligans ride bikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.21,0:10:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait until you turn 18 and\N get a proper driving license!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.19,0:10:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.18,0:10:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I even thought of \Nrunning away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey! Ai's never coming home, and it's all because of the horrible things I said to her!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.27,0:10:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's all your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.12,0:11:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything happens to her,\N we're getting a divorce!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.46,0:11:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ai, your mom was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.49,0:11:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind if you ride a bike or a tank! Please, just come home!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.17,0:11:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Or something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.54,0:11:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But I still got a license \Nwithout my mom knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.15,0:11:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You should've seen \Nthe look on Gun's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.23,0:11:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ta-da~!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.54,0:11:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It only took six hours to get here from Tokyo, but we're finally at Suzuka!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.67,0:11:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.09,0:11:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Suzuka Circuit is even \Nbigger than I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I want each of you to practice \Nwith your own goal in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.55,0:12:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,One more thing, we won't be measuring your times until this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.57,0:12:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for the time being, none of \Nyou will know how long you take.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.46,0:12:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But why not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.04,0:12:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just boring!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.60,0:12:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust you to object.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.45,0:12:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This rule was made \Nspecifically for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.61,0:12:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,By trying too hard to lower your time, your corner entries will suffer,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.35,0:12:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,your bike will become unstable, your corner exit\N will go to shit, and your times would just get worse. {if someone want me to explain this in mechanical/racing terms, lmk : )}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.01,0:12:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's your first time \Nat this kind of event,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.59,0:12:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know it'll \Ngo to your head,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.20,0:12:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so, instead, I want you\N to focus on your pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.92,0:12:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.29,0:12:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Dumbass. You really thought\N you'd post a time that easily? {no clue what he means by "show/demonstrate/give time"}{they tend to 'post' times on a leaderboard - which may only include top 20 or w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.38,0:12:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Suzuka ain't that easy. {/don't underestimate ...} {TLC, guess}{ye, is just  舐める }
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.98,0:12:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can take him! {makasen?}{is 抜かせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.26,0:13:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... he's already gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.87,0:13:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I going to do with them? \NI told them to take it easy on the first lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.48,0:13:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,His time on the West course has improved by two seconds since this morning. {ichikawa just said it's their first lap and we've heard him saying they'll only measure it in the afternoon so idk what's this about}{first lap post morning prac. session?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.91,0:13:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Gun's been sticking\N like glue to the guy in the white helmet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.07,0:13:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He's trying to learn the lines\N from a more experienced rider. {let's just call this paraphrased}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.25,0:14:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's finally over!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.79,0:14:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll settle this later! {TLC, not sure what he means: left showdown in one's custody - likely "let's postpone"}{I assume it's like 後をつける?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.27,0:14:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with that guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, he said he \Nhad somewhere to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.22,0:14:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go change, \Nbe back in a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.37,0:14:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry! {page 160}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.28,0:15:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,N-Now what do I do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.81,0:15:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I saw it all... All of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.51,0:15:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I'm... I mean... I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.96,0:15:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I didn't know you \Nwere changing in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.08,0:15:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take responsibility, and I'll \Ndo my best to make you happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.34,0:15:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have 21 payments left on my GP, b-but my \Nfamily owns a grocery store, so I've got a future! {GPのローンが後２１回とわれし、　う、うちらの八百屋も将来スーパーするし？ or at least something close to that I guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.75,0:15:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't cause you any trouble,\N so I'm ready to marry you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.34,0:15:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiro, take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.76,0:15:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to go that far.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.00,0:15:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Just forget about it, you idiot.{Isn't the pitch-accent of this wprd higher at the end to imply something? Unless I'm overthinking this}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.67,0:15:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doomed...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.42,0:15:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.53,0:15:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiro looked at Miyuki \Nwhen she was changing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.51,0:15:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! You saw \Nthe princess naked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.71,0:15:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he did a little\N more than that...{idk what the fuck is in his hand, and I'm not sure I want to know}{Looky likes a cat's paw, goes with his cat ears :^)}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.63,0:15:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I did not!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.30,0:15:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm innocent!\N I didn't do a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.81,0:16:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I really didn't know! \NI sure as hell didn't touch her!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.57,0:16:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, Mom, it's \Nbeen a while, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.42,0:16:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoyo is doing great.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.58,0:16:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We're still getting along fine,\N so don't worry about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.09,0:16:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was at Suzuka, and since\N I was in the neighborhood...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.57,0:16:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd best come \Nsee you before I went back. {VERY unsure what he means, TLC please Touge darling:smooch:, here's manga text, tho it doesn't seem entirely right: せやからどうないしても会って帰ろうと思ってな・・・･}{I assume the firstseya is just 世話 with a bitchin' accent?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.20,0:16:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have time to buy you \Nany flowers, so sorry 'bout that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.57,0:17:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! I got a flat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.75,0:17:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's strange, how'd I get \None all the way out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.57,0:17:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is the \NHijiri household.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.87,0:17:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.88,0:17:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Dad! Mom!\N- Dad! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.11,0:17:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.33,0:17:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.09,0:17:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, I gotta go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.09,0:17:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about \Nme on the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.77,0:17:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not the type of rider who'd have a\N crash on the Tomei Expressway, after all. {東名高速ごときで事故るようなヤワな乗り方はしてへんさがいに from manga}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.71,0:18:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been saying it's too cold out to be wearing \Na short-sleeved sailor uniform for a few days now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.06,0:18:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but now that the Sun's out,\N you get reminded of how hot it really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.90,0:18:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Though, when the boys disappear, \Nwe do something a little unladylike.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.39,0:18:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,While summer was hiding behind the rain clouds, \Nwe could tell it was just around the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.94,0:18:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.84,0:18:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't bring an umbrella?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.43,0:18:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, It wasn't\N raining this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.99,0:18:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, everyone knows to bring\N an umbrella at this time of year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.28,0:18:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The rain never \Nbothered me anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're out on your bike in the rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.19,0:18:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, it's no fun at first, but the drive home\N feels much better when you're soaked through.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.57,0:18:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiro, say...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.27,0:19:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll you do \Nafter graduation?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.31,0:19:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.94,0:19:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.02,0:19:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we decide on our path,\N it impacts our future, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.89,0:19:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we decide on something, \Ndo we lose out on other choices?{I feel like I could make this more poetic?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.03,0:19:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We're to graduate next spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.54,0:19:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mi...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.84,0:19:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll all go our separate ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.92,0:19:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If only time could stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.99,0:19:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'd make this \Nmoment last forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.84,0:19:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost the big day, Hideyoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.68,0:19:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That race has been the only thing \Non my mind for the last six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.06,0:19:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really know much about races,\Nbut all that matters to me is that you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.11,0:19:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If your bike is maintained and you stick to the rules, safety won't be an issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.21,0:19:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If I perform well there, \Nit'll be my shortcut to going pro. {last year, ichikawa said they'll promote him to B-class, I assume this had already happened and becoming a pro is the next step following it}{it's いい成績 w/ an accent }
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.57,0:19:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hideyoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.53,0:19:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it, \Njust let me do my thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.23,0:20:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the rain stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.83,0:20:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, it's so red!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.67,0:20:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.04,0:20:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Summer's here already.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.74,0:20:25.65,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5\fade(120,120)}The center line continues \Nall the way to the horizon.{空へと続いてるセンター・ライン}{all four lines taken from 01 RC version}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.65,0:20:34.57,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5\fade(120,120)}As you rest your chin on your hand, \NI can't take my eyes off you.  {頬づえつきながら あなたを見てる}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:42.50,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5\fade(120,120)}So before you fall asleep,\N please let me know one thing...{教えて このまま眠ったなら}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.50,0:20:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"Racers to starting positions" {TS later} {スタート位置 整列}{damn, I've got mad TS skills}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.07,0:20:51.89,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5\fade(120,120)}Would you kiss me for \Nlonger than your other girl?{あの娘より長いKissしてくれるの}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.99,0:20:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a move on{tbh no clue what's 行けや in kansai}, #2 rider. {volume 8 page 76}{it's like a "get a moce on" kinda thing in my head}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.47,0:20:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.47,0:20:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Cause I'm #1, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.53,0:21:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They only brought you here to prop up the machine for me, dumbass!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.50,0:21:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so? Then \NI'd better get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.25,0:21:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Gun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.91,0:21:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh shut up, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.54,0:21:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That little shit...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.83,0:21:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 40 more seconds under the scorching Sun\N before the race is underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.17,0:21:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The light will turn yellow\N ten seconds before start.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.57,0:21:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the signal will change to\N green and a "go" sign will be raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.06,0:21:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The eyes of the \Nworld are on Suzuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.02,0:21:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, second by second{TLC, actually not know what's this tokuikkoku}, \Nthe start time is approaching.{刻一刻?}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.74,0:22:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, at last, only ten seconds left! \NThe signal turned yellow!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.91,0:22:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Drivers on their marks! \NWe have 60 vehicles participating today!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.21,0:22:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The light turns green and the\N drivers make a run for their bikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.40,0:22:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, an accident just off the start line!\N Down goes bike number 37!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.86,0:22:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The lead group heads into \Nthe corner side-by-side.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.83,0:22:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In the lead, holding onto his \Npole position, #1, Okamoto! {cloth bib displaying a competitor's number; athlete's number​From German “Decken”} {don't really hear what's in the middle, translating lines from manga here}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.70,0:22:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they're entering the s-bends! {east course - which is where Suz 'starts' on  - is just a big string of s bends}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.89,0:22:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! #3 makes a break for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.01,0:23:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Bike #3, who had been neck-and-neck with #1, makes an overtake and seizes the lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.90,0:23:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Our opening lap is as \Nintense as any sprint race! {no clue what he means by sprint race in bike races, prolly means "driving as if it's a short-distance race at max speed"}{nah, sprint races are much shorter - and typically have more aggressive driving as tyre/fuel conservation/pit strats. don't really appear}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.43,0:23:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as they leave the cambered corner,\N the top group will approach the uphill section! {"A reverse bank refers to a portion of a road or circuit course where the inside of a curve is higher than the outside." - not sure what to call it in english, tasukete daddy touge }
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.59,0:23:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And the competition for \Nthe top is really heating up! {guess, TLC. By the way, I discovered that this section sounds much clearer on Collectr's LD version, but I still have no clue what's this arasai thing (arrow sign?) that became more fierce and only half-sure about "top" part; }{争い？}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.35,0:23:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Having just passed through the Dunlop gate,\N the top group is disappearing{as there's a short tunnel} into the West course! {I assume you've read https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suzuka_International_Racing_Course}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.73,0:23:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We're entering lap number seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.57,0:23:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No change to the top with bike #3, Matsui of \Nthe Hamamatsu Racing Team, leading the pack. {would assume it's the name}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.96,0:23:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Onto the second group:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.41,0:23:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooya on bike #2 and Onozuka on bike #5 are really fighting for their position.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.37,0:23:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Maehara on bike #34 seems to \Nhave come off around Degner.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.22,0:23:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,More info on that to come!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.39,0:23:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how's our team doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.11,0:23:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Hideyoshi is in 17th, with a lap time of 2 minutes 38.16 seconds. {I hope this 16 in the end means fractions of second}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.80,0:23:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.87,0:23:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Being measured as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.65,0:23:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,29th place. Time is 2 minutes 41.25 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.77,0:23:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think they're \Na bit overpace?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.37,0:23:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, how do you manage \Nto remain so calm?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.23,0:23:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Who said I was?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.05,0:23:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm dying to get out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.05,0:23:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't get on that bike,\N I think I'm gonna explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.47,0:24:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care how fast these other guys are,\N I'm not losing to any of 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.87,0:24:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No changes to the lead with Matsui on bike #3 leading the pack into lap 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.58,0:24:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He just clocked in\N another smooth lap! {to pile up; to heap up; to stack up; to put on top of another good (condition); going well; fine; smooth}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.54,0:24:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My watch has a time split of \Nthree seconds for second place.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.60,0:24:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, \Nhe's gained a huge lead! {Noun, Suru verb, Intransitive verb\N1. running alone; running solo​\NNoun, Suru verb, Intransitive verb\N2. having a large lead (over the others); being far ahead (of everyone else)}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.67,0:24:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But #2, Ooya, is hot on his heels!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.32,0:24:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And Onozuka isn't far \Nbehind on bike #5!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.75,0:24:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too hot... my throat's so dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.67,0:25:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd hoped the wind would \Ncool me down a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.75,0:25:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but with the heat reflecting off the asphalt, it's like I'm driving into an inferno.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.86,0:25:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little better if\N I stay beneath the cowl,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.59,0:25:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's still like I've been thrown into a frying pan where someone's turning up the heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.43,0:25:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hot... so hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.60,0:25:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, get ready to swap drivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.44,0:25:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ai, can you get the pit \Nsign out for Hideyoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.84,0:25:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.82,0:25:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Haga, get the charger ready. {hope I didn't mishear the name}{probs sound}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.63,0:25:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.42,0:25:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hagino, the board! {not sure what's it used for yet}{it's used to show where the bike should stop in the pits}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.51,0:25:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,On it right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.74,0:25:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And remember, once we're done \Nwith Hideyoshi, it's the princess' turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.86,0:25:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.20,0:25:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born ready! \NLeave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.71,0:25:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's lap 18 and the leader, Matsui, on bike #3 is coming in hot to the pit lane.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.71,0:25:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Their bike will be refueled \Nand their riders swapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.09,0:25:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And Onozuka, \N#5, isn't far behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.95,0:25:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the race leader becomes Ooya on bike #2, as he flies past the stands.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.03,0:25:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Followed by Yamada on bike #6.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.67,0:25:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hamamatsu Racing Team's\N pit work is as fast as ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.68,0:25:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're back on \Ntrack within five seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.69,0:26:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibe, the rider \Nreplacing Matsui, is off!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.87,0:26:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And here comes \NHijiri on bike #16!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.94,0:26:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, keep it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.53,0:26:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but I've been \Nwaiting a long time for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.72,0:26:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, Hideyoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.83,0:26:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's payback from the start line!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.80,0:26:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That asshole...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.22,0:26:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, what the hell was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.39,0:26:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.64,0:26:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.60,0:26:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you two playing at?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.41,0:26:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in the \Nmiddle of the race!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.81,0:26:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great pace. \NHow can you not love it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.07,0:27:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Charging is done!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.96,0:27:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Hiro, get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.40,0:27:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Miyuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.12,0:27:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.58,0:27:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The race has been \Ngoing for almost an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.71,0:27:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's maintained its \Nsprint-race-like pace!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.49,0:27:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Bike #3, Ibe from Hamamatsu Racing is\N in the lead and is entering his 23rd lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.87,0:27:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But Murakami, #5, from Suzuka Riding is about six seconds behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.98,0:27:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The lineup was just as we predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.33,0:27:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But something's happening \Nin the second group!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.85,0:27:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A rider just clocked in a blistering\Ntime of 2 minutes 35 seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.08,0:27:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ichinose Racing's #16 is really putting the pressure on the other riders!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.57,0:27:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so cool, #16!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.38,0:28:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The crowd's more excited to see \Nme than that reckless little runt! {TLC, I've just lost my will to live: この必殺カメが出てくっとやっぱ盛り上がるぜ! - this is from manga,}{I'd assume 必殺カメ is a nickname because he's 'slow and steady' like a turtle - whilst also violent? not 100% sure, but works as is}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.60,0:28:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Koma, on bike #16, just did a lap\N faster than Ibe who's leading the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.46,0:28:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa there! Bikes #11 and #50 \Ncollide on the entry to the chicane!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.37,0:28:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Will Koma get caught up in it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.16,0:28:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And he avoids them!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.93,0:28:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What's Koma's lap time \Ngoing to be this now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.87,0:28:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Koma{senshu}'s time just reported to us is... 2 minutes, 34.91 seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.83,0:28:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's amazing! He broke \Nthe 34 second barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.76,0:28:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That dude's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.84,0:28:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Who {\i1}is{\i0} that guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.42,0:28:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Check the entry list.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.71,0:28:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It says Koma on #16.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.36,0:28:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be the Ichinose Racing Team: Koma Gun and Hijiri Hideyoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.20,0:28:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They're both only 17!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.00,0:28:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so young!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.91,0:28:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, they're still \Nin high school?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.77,0:28:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Koma's making a move\N on Yamada in 4th place!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.69,0:28:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If you give him a target to \Nchase, he's unbelievably fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.41,0:28:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, if there's nobody in sight, you can't light a flame under him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.62,0:29:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's why he can't\N drive like this all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.65,0:29:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Has he always had this level of insight? \NOr has instinct brought him this far?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.84,0:29:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's on the pass or on the circuit,\N chasing and then blowing past them is his style.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.43,0:29:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And when that happens,\N he's insanely fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.40,0:29:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy's a natural sprinter.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.39,0:29:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, Hideyoshi, we're\N changing riders again. Get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.43,0:29:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.35,0:29:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{この鈴鹿耐久オートバイレースもうすでにお馴染みになりました。エフエム放送でもお楽しみになります。}{leads into next line as FM radio was just getting popular around that time?}The Suzuka Endurance Race is now so well \Nknown that you can listen to it on FM radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.32,0:29:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who have an FM radio receiver with them, please tune in to 78 MHz.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.12,0:29:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.64,0:29:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the deal with \Nyou and Hideyoshi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.81,0:29:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like it's saving us any \Ntime in the pits, you moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.11,0:29:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just how I say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.47,0:30:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Same goes for him too, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.77,0:30:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job. We're now running somewhere between 35th and 40th place. {volume 9 page 53}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.03,0:30:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Manager, what about Ichinose?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.79,0:30:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ichinose? I think \Nthey're sitting in 6th.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.39,0:30:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,6th place?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.47,0:30:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they were even \Nin third at one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.50,0:30:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Those guys were? \NI can hardly believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.58,0:30:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Takanezawa, I'll be blunt. \NForget about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.41,0:30:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're on a different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.71,0:30:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna hear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.26,0:30:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're giving up?! \NJust like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.88,0:30:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You really think I'd let those\N punks get all the attention?{ いい思いをする  - to have all the fun; to get the better part of the deal; to get the easy life​ - if anyone wants to reword}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.22,0:30:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui from the Hamamatsu \NRacing Team is still in first.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.03,0:30:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And Okamoto from Green \NGrass is just behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.61,0:30:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Onozuka on bike #5 is in third, but Hijiri \Non bike #16 is making use of his slipstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.57,0:30:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? That one seems interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.52,0:30:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That #16.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.61,0:30:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He's my sort of rider.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.28,0:30:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Bike #16?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.65,0:30:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mean the other rider?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.22,0:30:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That stupidly fast kamikaze novice?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.63,0:30:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I mean the shorter \None who's riding right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.08,0:31:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you see why?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.47,0:31:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the 40,000 spectators here,\N how many do you think know what he's doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.73,0:31:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Five? Nah, maybe two or \Nthree would be generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.68,0:31:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,While they're polar opposites,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.59,0:31:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if those two geniuses are a team, \NI think we could see #16 winning today.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.11,0:31:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That little shit\N thinks he's so smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.49,0:31:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That beanpole's riding it too hard on\N the engine, it can't take much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.45,0:31:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All I've gotta do is maintain our current position and not put too much strain on the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.36,0:31:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm able to keep up with the bike in front at only 80% power.{by slipstreaming etc}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.93,0:31:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna preserve as much \Nof the engine's power as I can,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.50,0:31:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,then it's all down to that beanpole and his explosive driving!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.89,0:31:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's strange. The princess \Nhasn't come around yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.06,0:31:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no way \Nshe'd miss the pit-in sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.86,0:32:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think something \Nhappened to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.10,0:32:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.69,0:32:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.37,0:32:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.96,0:32:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What just happened to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.71,0:32:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.36,0:32:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Corner 130R. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suzuka_International_Racing_Course#130R_corner}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.02,0:32:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, I came off.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.79,0:32:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I've gotta keep riding!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.57,0:32:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,At least your \Nbones are still intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.68,0:32:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you keep racing?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.85,0:32:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know... it hurts like \Nhell whenever I move it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.95,0:32:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've lost all strength in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.64,0:32:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.73,0:32:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage is needed to race, but a different kind of courage is needed to retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.59,0:32:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll respect whatever \Ndecision you make.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.32,0:32:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You two just have to work\N it out amongst{that's a word, so shut up spellcheck} yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.59,0:32:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.09,0:33:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it, Mi.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.05,0:33:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll adjust our time splits to\N keep your driving to a minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.40,0:33:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give it everything I've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.13,0:33:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We're finishing this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.98,0:33:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuckin' dipshit!{leaving this in for WoH}{WoH: Oh cool, I can go full f-bomb :^)}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.19,0:33:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Go die in a ditch!{or lost media yourself idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.91,0:34:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! The tires are \Nworn down already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.91,0:34:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That beanpole's riding has \Nturned these tires to shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.37,0:34:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious?! I bet everything I had on winning here today!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.07,0:34:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,To hell with relying \Non others after this! {unsure about first sentence, usually I'd think he means "I hate to look after the others more than this"}{これ以上単員の世話になるのはいや -  nah is first one imo}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.58,0:34:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,, I'll go pro my own way, \Nand I'll do it for Tomoyo! {unsure about first sentence, usually I'd think he means "I hate to look after the others more than this"}{これ以上単員の世話になるのはいや -  nah is first one imo}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.80,0:34:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've gotta win first!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.72,0:34:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ichinose's bike. \NJust who I've been waiting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.18,0:34:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,These tires are done for! They're stopping me from going on the throttle out of the corners. {TLC, not sure about any part of this, especially what's 開ける to do here, full sentence from manga: コーナーの立ち上がりで開けるのがどうしてもおくれる}{basically, slidy tyres make accel hard, and you've gotta accel out of a corner. ez}{also, I interpreted the akeru as opening up the throttle}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.21,0:34:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All because of his shitty driving! {突っ込み}{Gun charges into corners and wears them down faster, is basically jist of it}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.46,0:34:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.48,0:34:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.57,0:34:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.65,0:34:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,For both my summer...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.40,0:34:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And my dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.66,0:34:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.43,0:35:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.47,0:35:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He crashed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.58,0:35:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't gimme that shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.24,0:35:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the last person who'd ever \Ndo that! There's no way he would!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.63,0:35:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, but still...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.77,0:35:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, take it easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.72,0:35:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you! {oi kimi}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.72,0:35:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.86,0:35:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't touch me...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.70,0:35:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.14,0:35:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibe from Hamamatsu Racing Team is\N the race leader going into the 69th{nice} lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.15,0:35:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Murakami, #5, is back in second, and Yamada is back in third.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.82,0:35:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.63,0:35:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And here comes Hijiri, walking \Nhis bike around the final corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.25,0:35:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so heavy...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.79,0:35:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And here was me thinking racing bikes were\N designed to be light, but it's so damn heavy...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.69,0:35:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, why...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.61,0:35:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are my legs \Nmovin' on their own?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.55,0:36:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I bring it back to the pits,\N there ain't a thing they can do about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.93,0:36:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.63,0:36:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so far...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.98,0:36:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How come the pit \Nlane's so damn long...?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.55,0:36:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly even see straight...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.90,0:36:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Feels like my heart's about \Nto jump outta my chest...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.60,0:36:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I can quit now, \Nbut like hell I'm gonna...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.86,0:36:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that beanpole's \Nwaiting for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.83,0:36:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And until he gets it,\N there's no way in hell I'm stopping...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.75,0:36:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it, Hideyoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.18,0:36:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hijiri, you're almost there!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.21,0:36:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.07,0:36:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all yours...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.71,0:37:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Beanpole!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.15,0:37:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's mine alright...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.04,0:37:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never believe it!{lib ish#}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.00,0:37:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibe from Hamamatsu Racing has come off on the s-bends and lost his lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.38,0:37:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, Murakami on bike\N #5 takes the top position!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.10,0:37:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ai, when this race is over,\N let's go to the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.99,0:37:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.10,0:37:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Koma's back in the \Nrace after swapping in for Hijiri!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.40,0:37:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But with all the repairs, \Nhe's a whole lap behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.30,0:37:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibe of Hamamatsu Racing also managed to drag his bike back to the pits!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.63,0:37:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Here come the mechanics! \NWhat will they make of it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.11,0:37:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't push yourself \Ntoo hard, Princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.30,0:38:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Murakami leads into the 72nd lap and we've still got 44 bikes on the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.95,0:38:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The lineup of the top group \Nis really getting shaken up!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.26,0:38:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,With injuries like these, I'll try to stay on course for at least 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.01,0:38:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui on bike #3 is \Ncoming out of the pits.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.65,0:38:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's more than a \Nlap behind first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.17,0:38:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And Koma of the Ichinose Racing Team is\N charging down the main straight and after Matsui. {not sure what to make of 駆け下りる here}{it's just like 'charging down'}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.07,0:38:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Though, since they've both had accidents,\N they're both lagging behind the battle for first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.44,0:38:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hope they give it \Ntheir all until the very end!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.52,0:38:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a chance. No way \Nthey're gaining a whole lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.03,0:38:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But that #16 is crazy fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.99,0:38:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's really closing \Nthe gap on #3.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.38,0:38:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Mi!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.16,0:38:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.10,0:38:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He carves through the \Nwind like nobody else can.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.38,0:38:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He was like that \Nback then too...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.41,0:38:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Some would say \Nyou're born for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.07,0:38:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You've grown ever faster...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.51,0:39:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've done it \Nwithout looking back...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.97,0:39:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought I'd be \Nable to keep up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.99,0:39:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've always been \Nwatching you from behind, Gun.{ok, lmk if this sounds vaguely threatening}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.90,0:39:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1500)}It wasn't love I felt \Nfor you, but admiration.{cheeky fade}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.86,0:39:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,For their final rider change, Suzuka Riding is\N replacing Murakami with Onozuka, their ace rider.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.09,0:39:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Onozuka on bike #5 is now in the top position, and I don't think he's going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.88,0:39:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait! What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.99,0:39:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui on bike #3 is in 7th and has just \Nclocked in a lap time of 2 minutes 33.84!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.83,0:39:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And Koma on bike \N#16 isn't far behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.31,0:39:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,His time is 2 minutes...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.53,0:39:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and 32.74 seconds! \NHe broke the 32 second barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.46,0:39:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.47,0:39:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui and Koma are\N exiting the final corner!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.28,0:39:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with you?! \NWhy are you rooting for him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.89,0:39:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really that stupid?! \NWhat can he possibly do now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.87,0:39:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8} He doesn't stand a chance at catching up!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.33,0:39:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.70,0:39:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one that made #16 crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.31,0:39:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw something \Nat him, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.82,0:40:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.37,0:40:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Who threw that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.57,0:40:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stop that! It's dangerous! Please stop throwing things!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.25,0:40:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,With 40 minutes to go, \NOnozuka on #5 enters his 83rd lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.13,0:40:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui and Koma on lap 83 and have finally caught \Nup to Hanakawa in 5th place around the s-bends.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.60,0:40:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui cuts in on \Nthe cambered corner.{the corner leading into dunlop is uphill --> downhill crest that sticks out, so that's probs what he means by 逆バンク}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.93,0:40:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.10,0:40:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,After overtaking Hanakawa on bike #7, Matsui \Nand Koma have once again climbed the rankings.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.48,0:40:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No blocks seem to\N stop their combination!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.53,0:40:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Matsui for you! He cuts \Npast Gouda on bike #21! {would assume 剛田}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.33,0:40:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Matsui's gone wide \Nand Koma takes his chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.56,0:40:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And #16 overtakes #3!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.00,0:40:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That kid's got drive. Things \Nare really starting to heat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.92,0:41:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.32,0:41:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ichikawa, if Gun keeps \Nthe pace of his last lap{\fscx200}—
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.61,0:41:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll make his way \Nto the front again.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.99,0:41:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And #3 makes a break for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.56,0:41:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it... I'll overtake you \Nas many times as I have to!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.77,0:41:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he is a runt, \Nhe still got the bike back to me.{kinda truncated "with short arms and legs"}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.83,0:41:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He was battered, broken,\N and could hardly breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.29,0:41:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And you thought I'd run out of steam here?! No fuckin' way!{swearing now and then is fun, so fuck you}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.50,0:41:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, Yamada in 3rd starts feeling \Nbikes #3 and #16 nip at his heels! {TLC, this "se wo fumiakasu" part just evades my brain}{is it not  脅かす ?}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.87,0:41:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Both are trying to break into the lead with bike 6 between them!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.38,0:41:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, they entered their 90th lap! With just \Nunder 13 minutes until the checkered flag is waved! {actually doesn't say flag but I assume}{ye, is fine}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.85,0:41:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Bikes #3 and #16 are closing \Nin on Shigeno in second place.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.81,0:41:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They're closing the gap \Nthrough the Casio triangle!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.93,0:42:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the three bikes are exiting the \Nfinal corner! It's anybody's game! {I hope he means this by "it's out of control"}{手がすく w/ potential or passive --> polite negative }{but let's just call this 'liberal'}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.98,0:42:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared... but \NI'm not sure why...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.61,0:42:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.84,0:42:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody can keep up with \NHamamatsu on the back straight!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.80,0:42:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But #65 is still fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.77,0:42:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year, Shigeno on bike #65 \Nhad to retire after a crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.31,0:42:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But this year, he's aiming \Nfor the championship!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.36,0:42:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The leader, Onozuka,\N is 20 seconds ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.53,0:42:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but here comes Koma!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.19,0:42:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He's giving it his all, \Nbut he can't break out!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.20,0:42:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.16,0:42:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddammit! \NNext time, you're mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.04,0:42:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, Koma's \Ngoing in too hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.25,0:42:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.25,0:42:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a crash!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.46,0:42:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, he regained control! \NNow Koma's driving like a true GP racer! {/riding is same level as; equal to; equivalent to; on par with grand prix}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.46,0:42:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In five minutes, the checkered flag will\N fly for this four-hour life-or-death race!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.73,0:42:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The race enters its final stretch!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.06,0:43:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.52,0:43:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt about it! \NThat's #5 in first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.52,0:43:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Bikes #3 and #16 are really \Npiling on the pressure!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.91,0:43:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Bike #5 can already feel \Nthem breathing down his neck!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.91,0:43:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.07,0:43:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Those guys are something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.37,0:43:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.15,0:43:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly take my eyes off them...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.33,0:43:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe how cool they are...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.04,0:43:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all or nothin'! How \Nmuch cooler could they get?!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.21,0:43:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The final lap! {imma pretend I can't hear that wasei-eigo shit, kthx}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.88,0:43:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Onozuka is making a break for it,\N but Matsui and Koma are close behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.31,0:43:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come too far to\N be overtaken now!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.44,0:43:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Their only chance \Nwill be on 130R!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.44,0:43:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever takes \Nthe inside line wins!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.20,0:44:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.95,0:44:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get much \Nmore inside than this!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.85,0:44:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're moments away from\N seeing the checkered flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.81,0:44:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'll be in the lead on \Nthe exit of the final corner?!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.73,0:44:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it be Koma, or Matsui?!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.69,0:44:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And #16's in the lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.66,0:44:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea! I can see the sea \Njust beyond the first corner! {honestly, no clue why he says daiichi, like the first in what? maybe "the last?"; TLC}{as it's 'beyond the first corner' as the first corner is at the end of the straight}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.58,0:44:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My throat's so dry... it's killing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.54,0:44:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui is attempting a breakout!\N Will he manage?! Will he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.21,0:44:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it be Koma or Matsui?!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.77,0:45:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And across the line! {honestly, this doesn't sound like something appropriate for auto racing, but idk what's realy said there and if anything touge would know that better than me right}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.52,0:45:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's all she wrote!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.89,0:45:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The winners are the\NHijiri-Koma pair on bike #16!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.52,0:45:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.26,0:45:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ichinose Racing Team!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.37,0:45:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Way to go! {idk what touge was expecting me to write here >_>; interesting fact: they removed the girl's shout here completely in the movie ver}{it's just "iiwayo!" smh}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.95,0:45:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That was amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.68,0:45:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.68,0:46:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This can't be real...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.34,0:46:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You're really somethin', \Nyou know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.23,0:47:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A man among men.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.60,0:47:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Look who's talkin'. If you weren't \Nmy partner, then we wouldn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.06,0:47:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,be standing here right now.{lit: be the winners}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.42,0:47:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe he'd say that... a man who'd \Nrather drop dead than give me a compliment... {抜かしやがった。。。死んでもお世辞なんて言わん男が。。。from manga, no clue what he means because of course it's so hard to name the sentence object, so TLC it is}{抜かしやがった can be 'to talk' as well in a vulgar way, and that'd make more sense - maybe he's going for a little poetic wordplay?}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.91,0:47:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a good guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.00,0:47:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the sort you'd \Nfind anywhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.42,0:47:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did I always \Nhate him so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.72,0:47:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the best guy I ever met...{lit: in world}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.53,0:47:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Beanpole...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.51,0:48:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Beanpole, you've gotta \Nget faster than that. {unsure he means this, maybe "I went before you" or idk}{honestly, could go wither way, but I like this interpretation}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.75,0:48:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hideyoshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.30,0:48:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hideyoshi... I'll get faster...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.42,0:48:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you wanted, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.55,0:48:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what I heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.25,0:49:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, you gonna enter \Nthe final race at Tsukuba? {when I ctrlf wiki with 最終戦 it's apparently some race which is held in multiple rounds where by winning previous one you're permitted to join the next one}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.59,0:49:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to for a B-class license.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.78,0:49:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already missed \Nthe entry deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.89,0:49:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, it's been dealt with.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.53,0:49:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hideyoshi said you'd probably \Ncome around, so I signed you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.28,0:49:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.81,0:49:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Gun, how about you ride \Naround on Hideyoshi's bike from now on?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.30,0:49:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be an easy fix.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.05,0:49:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.24,0:49:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I could never do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.21,0:49:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.31,0:49:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,His blood, sweat, and \Ntears went into this Katana.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.84,0:49:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I could ride that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.22,0:49:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.85,0:49:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's riding it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.35,0:50:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the only thing\N Hideyoshi left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.73,0:50:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What will we say\N to Tomoyo now?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.14,0:50:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't bear to let \Nsomeone else ride it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.00,0:50:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but I also couldn't bear to see it gather dust in the corner of some garage...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.36,0:50:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.62,0:50:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They can be together now.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.54,0:50:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all yours, Hideyoshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.75,0:50:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Not once did I manage \Nto overtake your Katana...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.72,0:50:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But you quit while you\N were ahead, you dumbass...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.73,0:50:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, my memories\N of you are gone. {no clue what he means to say by "I don't remember you"}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.78,0:50:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll forget you in no time. \NSee you around, Hideyoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.20,0:50:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget to give 'em hell! {ends on a cringe line... smh}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.65,0:51:15.14,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}Even if it's been raining all morning, {たとえ朝からの雨に}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.32,0:51:23.21,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}and even if it feels like it's \Ngonna be damp all day, {湿気そうな一日が来ても}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.27,0:51:32.03,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}I won't let the mirror reflecting \Nmy sleepy face go cloudy. {眠い顔を映したミラーまで曇らせない}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.03,0:51:39.70,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}Don't go thinking I won't pick\N out my favorite clothes! {好きな服を選んでみるのも諦めない}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.70,0:51:45.50,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}My bobby socks and my \NMary Jane shoes... {ボビーソックス　メリージェーンシューズ}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.33,0:51:52.99,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}always give me a spring in my step. {はねをあげて歩くのもいいね}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.38,0:52:01.97,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}When a nice pair of red-calf \Ngloves fit you perfectly, {赤いカーフの手袋みたいにピタリ来れば}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.97,0:52:12.32,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}you worry more about your\N looks than your feelings! {気分よりも　カラダで自分を意識してるよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.48,0:52:21.02,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}You're not going anywhere if you keep \Nyour heart closed, so it's up to you. {心閉ざしてたら　始まらない It's up to you}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.02,0:52:30.57,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}My path ahead is uncertain, but I keep \Nwalking as time won't wait for me.   {見知らぬ未来へ続く時は止められない}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.89,0:52:41.58,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}I've always been afraid to disappoint. {いつも怖かった　ディサポイント}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.68,0:52:49.30,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}But if I have the courage to face it, {見つめてゆく勇気さえあれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.56,0:52:54.38,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}my shyness and shame won't hold me back, {ShyとShameかかげた}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.38,0:52:58.31,Songs,,0,0,0,,{\fade(250,250)}and I could throw away my old smile. {ほほ笑み捨ててもいい}
